“Bridging the gap” 7” x 20”
All of my works have a narrative that is personal to me but also one that is universal. This piece is about climate change, but it’s also very much about changes that happen within a family and a relationship. In our day to day lives, my husband and I are both so busy it often feels like we get detached from one another so easily. We are the bears in this piece. The blue balloon in the middle represents our son, as he is the center of our world. We pull the threads to bridge the gaps between us, keeping everything together even when it feels challenging. I love this piece 🥰

#intaglio #etching #printmaking #mixedmedia #polarbear #climatechange #balloon #icefloe #bridgingthegap #contemporaryart #contemporaryprintmaking #narrativeart #drawing #pencildrawing

“Regaining Your Color” 23” x 35.5”
I don’t often share the stories behind my pieces because I like when people interpret it in their own way- however, this piece was a real joy to work on and means a lot to me so I thought I’d share. When flamingos have young, they lose the color in their plumage because they are giving all their nutrients and care to their children. As their young get older and start to feed themselves, they regain their brilliant pink color. I think this is a beautiful metaphor for parenthood and what the transition feels like from babyhood to the toddler years. In this work, there are 8 balloon flamingos. When we were trying to have a child (on our long, long journey through IVF) we had 8 embryos throughout our various cycles- each a possibility of a child, but only one stuck around (our magical little 2.5 year old, Wellsie). Balloons symbolize memory in my work, and the way we chose to hold onto things or let things go. This piece is about my journey back to feeling myself again after many difficult years of my reproductive career. 

#intaglio #etching #printmaking #painting #flamingo #ivf #parenthood #mixedmedia #contemporaryart #contemporaryprintmaking #stlouisartfair #motherhood

Making etchings is so fun. Once I have the drawing in my hard ground coated copper complete, I put it in the acid, clean the hard ground off, saw it out and file it, then ink and - the best part- print it!! Now, hear me out…. Next up, a giant beetle etching?

The first layer of etching on my seal plate is done! If you want to see a longer form video of this and hear me talk you through each step, check out my highlighted story “seal etching”. #intaglio #etching #printmaking #seal #harborseal #softgroundetching

How do I shape my etching plates? I saw them out by hand with a jewelers saw, then I file all the edges. It’s a long process but it allows me to have the freedom to reimagine what is happening in the picture plane around my etching every time I print it 🤗
